  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 889faa658c7b2c94ea4fff939bf8022e, type: 3}
  m_Name: DialogNPCArmourer
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Patrizio
  Icon: {fileID: 7416670922274956215, guid: 67e11902f9a599344b5dc2f4b5a33db5, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 0
  Greeting: Patrick The Armourer (MARCELLO 11LABS)
  Day1Dialog:
  - "You ever hold iron straight from the forge? My father put my hands to it when
    I was younger than you are now. Hinges, nails, blades for men who thought a good
    sword made them safe.\nHere, I make things that send men straight back into fire.
    I tell myself it helps \u2014 I have to \u2014 but we both know it just buys
    a little time.\nLook at the guns. They\u2019re wild now. Give them a day, they\u2019ll
    start finding our walls. Then we see what holds."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Pick up a dented breastplate, you can tell how someone met the ground. This
    was has a hole right through the heart and out the back \u2014 musket ball. You
    start reading deaths without names.\nBy tomorrow I\u2019ll be able to recognise
    which pieces I made. I don\u2019t think anyone wants that kind of memory."
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Yesterday I told you the guns would settle. They have \u2014 you heard it.\nA
    helmet I made came back. Hole right through the brow. He probably lifted his
    head just to breathe. You don\u2019t get second chances with that.\nTomorrow,
    I\u2019ll know my own work before I turn it over. That\u2019s when it gets inside
    your head."
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - "I used to work in Birgu. My father still does, even though his hands shake.
    He always said an armourer keeps people safe.\nOut here? We fix armour and sharpen
    swords while they\u2019re still warm from someone else\u2019s blood, us or theirs.
    If that\u2019s safety, it\u2019s not the kind he meant."
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - "You remember that helmet story? Today I scraped skin out of a gorget seam. Little
    strands of hair stuck in the hinge.\nOil washes off easy, but blood seems to
    stay. I scrub and scrub and when I look at my hands, they still look red and
    tainted with blood.\nGive it another day \u2014 I won\u2019t feel anything at
    all."
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Hear that pattern? Someone out there knows what he\u2019s doing. More shots
    are finding their way inside the fort.\nMy repairs don\u2019t comfort anyone
    anymore. All I\u2019m doing is stretching out their fear. I\u2019m not scared
    to die. I just don\u2019t want to keep a man alive long enough to hurt more."
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - "It\u2019s strange seeing a familiar face. Most change into bodies or parts before
    you get a second look.\nThose walls shook hard. Men shook harder. Someone experienced
    joined the other side \u2014 you can feel it in the pacing of the shots.\nI don\u2019t
    think this place was built to last through someone like that."
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - "You come on a day where there\u2019s almost nothing to fix. Not because we\u2019re
    ready \u2014 because we\u2019re running out of people with chests to strap iron
    onto.\nCrossings are watched. Birgu might as well be a world away. I used to
    think I\u2019d make it back.\nNow I just want to stop hearing metal scream."
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "You\u2019re still here. Good. I keep turning and expecting no one at all.\nHalf
    the men are gone. The rest look like they\u2019re waiting their turn. I used
    to think my work kept them alive \u2014 gave them a chance.\nNow it just keeps
    them awake long enough to feel the end coming."
  Day1Audio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 385a710762871c2408649f7bd2f02ca3, type: 3}
  Day2FirstTimeAudio: {fileID: 8300000, guid: f64655f348efbff488bf963e559dc4b4, type: 3}
